					  Mastran Aces a Par 4 at the Summit County Am — But Doesn’t Get a Skin!  

					 by Allen Freeman  |  August 6, 2011    No Comments  

					 

 Michael Mastran made what might be the shot of his life in Saturday’s first round of the 2011 Summit County Amateur at Good Park Golf Course in Akron.  
 With the tees moved up to 270 yards to entice players into going for the par-4 green at the 12th hole, Mastran flew his tee shot with a driver directly at the tucked front-left ‘sliver’ position and landed his ball right behind the hole. The ball bounced up, and from the tee the group thought the ball flown over the very small corner of the green.   [Read more ?]  

					 

					   

			

					
			

