					  Aaron Crewse Jumps Out to First Round Lead at 2009 Summit County Am  

					 by Allen Freeman  |  August 1, 2009    No Comments  

					 

 Aaron Crewse of Cuyahoga Falls grabbed the first round lead of the 2009 Summit County Amateur Golf Championship at Good Park Golf Course on Saturday, posting a roller-coaster 3-under par 68 to lead by two shots going into Sunday’s finish. 
 Crewse birdied his first two holes of the day and his last two holes of the day, and in between made two more birdies, a bogey and a double-bogey on the tenth. Regardless, it was enough positive scores to earn a two shot lead over Anthony Yacovazzi. 
 25 players posted rounds of 74 or better, so given the wet conditions and expected wind tomorrow, the finale should be a barn-burner. 
  Plain Dealer recap here ;  Akron Beacon Journal story here . 
